title: Far North sets scene for new ad
text:
Tourism Tropical North Queensland part of new campaign to market FNQ by: What are these? STUNNING: Felicity Laurie from the Gold Coast explores the reef off Green Island near Cairns. PICTURE: LUKE MARSDEN Source: News Corp Australia 
FILM crews are in the Far North taking footage of the region’s aquatic gems to be included in the new marketing campaign. 
Tourism Tropical North Queensland chief executive Alex de Waal said the marketing body had been “working quietly behind the scenes” with Tourism Australia on the filming of Cairns and Great Barrier Reef and rainforest components of a television commercial. 
He said four TTNQ member’s products were featured but would not name them. 
“The Cairns gateway to the World Heritage-listed Great Barrier Reef and rainforest will feature prominently and given today’s (Wednesday) weather, the footage will be amazing,” Mr de Waal said.
